#: ../../B/blit.rst:5
msgid "blit"
msgstr "blit"

#: ../../B/blit.rst:7
msgid "/blit/, vt\\."
msgstr "/blit/, 他動詞"

#: ../../B/blit.rst:10
msgid ""
"[common] To copy a large array of bits from one part of a computer's memory "
"to another part, particularly when the memory is being used to determine "
"what is shown on a display screen. \"The storage allocator picks through the"
" table and copies the good parts up into high memory, and then blits it all "
"back down again.\" See :ref:`bitblt`\\, :ref:`BLT`\\, :ref:`dd`\\, "
":ref:`cat`\\, :ref:`blast`\\, :ref:`snarf`\\. More generally, to perform "
"some operation (such as toggling) on a large array of bits while moving "
"them."
msgstr ""
"[一般的]コンピューターのメモリのある部分から別の部分へ、ビットの大きな配列を複製すること。特に、そのメモリが表示画面に何を映すかを決めるのに使われている場合に言う。「ストレージアロケータはテーブルを調べて良い部分を高位メモリへコピーし、それからまた全部を下へblitし戻す」。\\"
" :ref:`bitblt`\\ 、\\ :ref:`BLT`\\ 、\\ :ref:`dd`\\ 、\\ :ref:`cat`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`blast`\\ 、\\ :ref:`snarf`\\ "
"を参照。より一般的には、ビットの大きな配列を移動させながらそれに何らかの操作(トグルなど)を行うこと。"

#: ../../B/blit.rst:16
msgid ""
"[historical, rare] Sometimes all-capitalized as BLIT: an early experimental "
"bit-mapped terminal designed by Rob Pike at Bell Labs, later commercialized "
"as the AT&T 5620. (The folk etymology from \"Bell Labs Intelligent "
"Terminal\" is incorrect. Its creators liked to claim that \"Blit\" stood for"
" the Bacon, Lettuce, and Interactive Tomato.)"
msgstr ""
"[歴史的、まれ]時にBLITとすべて大文字で書かれる。Bell LabsのRob Pikeが設計した初期の実験的なビットマップ端末で、のちにAT&T "
"5620として商用化された。(「Bell Labs Intelligent "
"Terminal」という俗説の語源は誤り。製作者たちは「Blit」がBacon, Lettuce, and Interactive "
"Tomato(ベーコン、レタス、対話型トマト)の略だと言い張るのを好んだ。)"
